<section class="quick-guide"> 
  <div class="flex">
    <div class="flex-third registration--starter">
      <h4>Registration</h4>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="https://auburn-csm.symplicity.com/employers/?signin_tab=2" target="_blank">Click here to create a new employer account.</a></li>
        <li>Complete your company profile.</li>
        <li>You may select “All Majors” under the Majors Recruited section.</li>
        <li>Submit.</li>
        <li>Allow at least one business day for the Career Center to verify your registration.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-third">
      <h4>Post jobs</h4>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="https://auburn-csm.symplicity.com/employers/index.php?signin_tab=0">Click here to log in.</a><br/><span class="muted">Username: your email address<br/>Password: will be emailed to you</span></li>
        <li>Navigate to the Jobs tab and click "Add New."</li>
        <li>Select “Post to this school only.”</li>
        <li>Complete job description and submit.<br /><span class="muted">To re-open an old posting, select “Show Archived” under the Copy Existing category.</span></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-third">
      <h4>Student eligibility requirements</h4>
      <p>
        To be hired as a student employee, the student must either 
        presently enrolled in at least one semester hour, or have 
        been enrolled last semester with plans to enroll next semester.
      </p>
      <h4>Guidelines for work hours</h4>
      <p>
        Up to 20 hours per week (0.50 FTE) while enrolled for
        <strong>all campus jobs combined</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content extra-content content--no-padding content--guide">
  <h3 class="how-to-header padding">How to Hire</h3>
  <p>Mouse over the numbers below for additional details.</p>
  <ul class="guide">
    <li class="guide-step">
      <a class="icon" 
         role="button" 
         tabindex="0" 
         data-html="true" 
         data-trigger="hover" 
         data-placement="top" 
         data-toggle="popover"  
         data-content=
         "<ol>
            <li>Log in<p class='muted'>Username: your email address</p><p class='muted'>Password: will be emailed to you</p></li>
            <li>Navigate to the Jobs tab and click &quot;Add New&quot;</li>
            <li>Select &quot;Post to this school only&quot;</li>
            <li>Complete job description and submit</li>
          </ol>
          <p class='muted'>To re-open an old posting, select “Show Archived” under the Copy Existing category.</p>"
         ></a>
      <div class="details">Post positions on <a href="https://auburn-csm.symplicity.com/employers/index.php?signin_tab=0">TRL</a></div>
    </li>
    <li class="guide-step">
      <a class="icon" 
         role="button" 
         tabindex="0" 
         data-html="true" 
         data-trigger="hover" 
         data-placement="top" 
         data-toggle="popover" 
         data-content=
         "<p>
            It is recommended that employers interview applicants 
            before extending an offer of employment. In taking the 
            time to make a more informed decision, employers will 
            keep employees longer and find a better return in their 
            investment.
          </p>"
         ></a>
      <div class="details">Interview applicants and select your student worker(s)</div>
    </li>
    <li class="guide-step">
      <a class="icon" 
         role="button" 
         tabindex="0" 
         data-html="true" 
         data-trigger="hover" 
         data-placement="top" 
         data-toggle="popover" 
         data-content=
         "<p>
            See Tips & Advice section below for more details.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Login in to AU Access</li>
            <li>Click on the Employee Services tab</li>
            <li>Scroll down to the Student Schedule Quick Links</li>
            <li>Click on “View/Print Student Schedules”</li>
            <li>Select the term</li>
            <li>Use the student’s banner ID to access schedule</li>
          </ol>"
         ></a>
      <div class="details">Determine student enrollment</div>
    </li>
    <li class="guide-step">
      <a class="icon" 
         role="button" 
         tabindex="0" 
         data-html="true" 
         data-trigger="hover" 
         data-placement="top" 
         data-toggle="popover" 
         data-content=
         "<ol>
            <li>Review the PEAEMPL screen in Banner Admin.</li>
            <li>Type in the Banner ID# and click “Next Block.”</li>
            <li>Review the Employee Status </li>
            <li>Note the status; it should state “Active” or “Terminated.”</li>
          </ol>
          <h4>Active</h4>
          <p>
            The number of hours the student can work will need to be determined.
            Complete an ePAF through Banner to add the new job.
          </p>
          <h4>Terminated or New Hire</h4>
          <p>
            The student will need to fill out all paperwork. 
            Send all completed paperwork to Human Resources.
          </p>"
         ></a>
      <div class="details">Determine hiring status (active, new-hire, terminated)</div>
    </li>
    <li class="guide-step">
      <a class="icon" 
         role="button" 
         tabindex="0" 
         data-html="true" 
         data-trigger="hover" 
         data-placement="top" 
         data-toggle="popover" 
         data-content=
         "<p>
            See Tips and Advice below for more information.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              View the NBIJLST screen in Banner Admin 
              <p class='muted'>
                Current jobs will have a Begin Date entered and the End Date field will be blank.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>Double-click on the Position box and the NBAJOBS screen will open</li>
            <li>Click “Next Block” to see the Job FTE for that position</li>
            <li>If the student holds multiple current positions, go back to NBIJLST and repeat these instructions</li>
            <li>Subtract the current FTE from .50 to get the number of hours the student can work in your position</li>
          </ol>"
         ></a>
      <div class="details">Determine the number of hours the student can work</div>
    </li>
    <li class="guide-step">
      <a class="icon" 
         role="button" 
         tabindex="0" 
